.TH "watch\-xsel" 1  "2014\-12\-22" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "@PACKAGE_NAME@"

.SH "NAME"
watch\-xsel \- Watch X11 selection and print it on on stdout (filters optinoal)

.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.B "watch\-xsel"
.I "[...options...]"

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.B "watch\-xsel"
watches the X11 selection and print it on stdout when it changes (possibly filtered). If stdout is redirected into a file, the results are also printed on stderr.

.SH "OPTIONS"

.TP
.BR \-\-help
Print usage information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Print version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-unique
Ignore the new value if it has been printed before
.TP
.BR \-\-urls
Only pass URLs (ftp, http, https)

